BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Connect Mat-Su": "https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/the-roaming-playroom-together-time-at-lekker-coffee-10/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:connect_matsu
X-SOURCE:Connect Mat-Su
DTSTART;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260328T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260328T163000
DTSTAMP:20260321T180057
CREATED:20260309T193801Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260322T012212Z
UID:10012864-1774708200-1774715400@www.connectmatsu.org
SUMMARY:The Roaming Playroom: "Together Time" at Lekker Coffee
DESCRIPTION:That Thing Goin On is excited to announce a new community offering: The Roaming Playroom!\nThe Roaming Playroom will be hosting weekly “Together Time” at Lekker Coffee and Baking Co right in downtown Palmer.\n“Together Time” means sharing life in shared spaces – where grownups stay\, kids play\, and community grows.\nThe Roaming Playroom curates pop-up play spaces for parents to slow down\, eat\, and drink in public without rushing\, while also spending quality time with their children and connecting with other community members.\nStarting March 10\, come visit us at Lekker Coffee and Baking Co on:\nTuesdays from 12:30pm-2:30pm\nand\nSaturdays from 2:30pm-4:30pm\nYou bring your people\, I’ll bring my people\, and lets build some community together!
URL:https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/the-roaming-playroom-together-time-at-lekker-coffee-10/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://www.connectmatsu.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/The-roaming-playroom.webp
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Connect Mat-Su": "https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/not-so-creepy-creatures-kens/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:connect_matsu
X-SOURCE:Connect Mat-Su
DTSTART;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260328T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260328T183000
DTSTAMP:20260321T180057
CREATED:20260317T214409Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260322T012211Z
UID:10012890-1774719000-1774722600@www.connectmatsu.org
SUMMARY:Not So Creepy Creatures @ Ken's
DESCRIPTION:🐍 Not So Creepy Creatures\nA Free Live Creature Experience at Ken’s\nThink you’re brave enough? 👀\nJoin us at Ken’s Garden Center for a wild and fascinating evening with Ken & Aaron as they introduce some of nature’s most misunderstood critters.\nFrom snakes and spiders to other creepy-crawly friends\, you’ll get the chance to see these amazing creatures up close and learn why they’re actually important (and not so scary after all!).\nThis fun\, educational experience is perfect for curious kids\, brave adults\, and anyone ready to face their fears.\nWhat to Expect\n🕷 Live creature demonstrations\n🐍 Learn about reptiles\, insects\, and other misunderstood animals\n🦎 Fun facts and surprising science\n🙌 Opportunities for brave volunteers to interact\nAll presented by Bugged by Aaron.\nEvent Details\n📅 March 10 & March 28\n⏰ 5:30 PM\n📍 Ken’s Garden Center – Wasilla\n🎟 FREE Event\nNo registration required — just come ready for some creepy fun!\nWho Should Come\n• Families and kids who love animals\n• Anyone curious about reptiles and insects\n• People ready to challenge their fears\n• Nature lovers\nKen’s Tip 🌿\nMany of these creatures actually help gardens thrive by controlling pests and supporting healthy ecosystems.\nSo come get your “icks” out with us and leave with a new appreciation for the wild side of nature.
URL:https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/not-so-creepy-creatures-kens/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://www.connectmatsu.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/creepy-creatures-3.28.26.webp
END:VEVENT
