UID:10012870-1775296800-1775322000@www.connectmatsu.org
SUMMARY:Easter Egg Hunt at Ken's!
DESCRIPTION:🌸🥚 KEN’S ANNUAL EASTER EGG HUNT IS BACK! 🥚🌸\nJoin us for one of our most beloved family traditions at Ken’s Garden Center!\n📅 Saturday\, April 4\, 2026\n🕙 10am–5pm\n🥚 Egg Hunts EVERY HOUR on the hour!\n🎟️ FREE for the whole family\nOver 150\,000 eggs hidden throughout the greenhouses! 🌿\n📸 Bunny pictures\n🎉 Family games\n🌷 Greenhouses open\n🔥 Barbecue babes\nSpots fill up quickly — please register your family in advance at:\n👉 www.kensgardencenter.com\nIt’s free — we just need to know you’re coming so we can plan the fun! 💛\nTag your Easter crew and start planning your outfits 🐰🌸\nWe can’t wait to see our community fill the greenhouse again!
URL:https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/easter-egg-hunt-at-kens/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://www.connectmatsu.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/kens-egg-hunt-4.4.26.webp
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Visit Palmer": "https://visitpalmer.com/event/the-krrbrrr/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:visit_palmer
X-SOURCE:Visit Palmer
DTSTART;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260404T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260404T170000
DTSTAMP:20260321T180104
CREATED:20260221T163737Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260221T163737Z
UID:8008-1775296800-1775322000@visitpalmer.com
SUMMARY:The KrrBrrr
DESCRIPTION:Come join us for the 9th annual Krrbrrr! Spend an hour or a day–or anything in between–trail running with your closest running friends and nemeses; very low key.Distance options: Approx. 5–mile loops (with optional 2.5 mile loop); run as many as you please in the 8hr time period\, until you can’t feel your limbs\, or until you can’t give any more blood.Course has variety of flat\, steep\, rolling\, wide\, double-wide\, and single-track trails. Slush\, slop\, mud\, ice\, poop (horse variety)\, thorns\, blood\, views\, guaranteed.Newcomers: If you’re looking for a polished\, hand held\, catered race…you’ve come to the wrong place. This is just an excuse to run through the mud and shake the cobwebs off your winter brain. Sign-ups after March 6 are NOT guaranteed a shirt.This year the KrrBrrr is excited to announce we will be donating a portion of the race proceeds to the Mat-Su Sentinel\, a nonprofit news website with free\, community-based news for Mat-Su. \nJim Creek\n352 N Chugach St\, Palmer
URL:https://visitpalmer.com/event/the-krrbrrr/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Visit Palmer": "https://visitpalmer.com/event/%f0%9f%8c%b7-april-1st-saturday-vendor-market-celebrate-spring-with-local-creativity-%f0%9f%8c%b7/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:visit_palmer
X-SOURCE:Visit Palmer
DTSTART;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260404T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260404T170000
DTSTAMP:20260321T180104
CREATED:20260221T164201Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260221T164201Z
UID:8012-1775296800-1775322000@visitpalmer.com
SUMMARY:🌷 April 1st Saturday Vendor Market – Celebrate Spring with Local Creativity! 🌷
DESCRIPTION:Spring is in the air\, and the April 1st Saturday Vendor Market is the perfect place to celebrate! Join us for a day filled with local talent\, handmade treasures\, and delicious treats — all created and shared by amazing Alaskan makers.\nExplore crochet and knit items\, hand-dyed yarns\, and hand-sewn bags\, wallets\, and purses. Discover stone and gem jewelry\, handcrafted pens\, and unique laser-engraved gifts\, plus leather goods\, D&D and pride items\, and embroidered creations like bags\, patches\, and apparel.\nEnjoy the flavors of Alaska with fermented and freeze-dried foods\, sourdough stuffed breads\, cookies\, brownies\, and other baked treats. Don’t miss elderberry syrup and natural products\, candles made from barrel staves\, and stunning stained glass art to brighten your home.\nYou’ll also find polymer clay dragons\, greeting cards\, pet treats and toys\, plus info on chiropractic and massage services and cell phone and TV options.\nWhen you’re ready for a bite\, grab a meal from one of our three local food trucks and enjoy the community spirit that makes this market special!\n Shop Local • Support Makers • Celebrate Spring \n350 E Dahlia Ave\, Palmer
URL:https://visitpalmer.com/event/%f0%9f%8c%b7-april-1st-saturday-vendor-market-celebrate-spring-with-local-creativity-%f0%9f%8c%b7/
END:VEVENT
