BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Visit Palmer": "https://visitpalmer.com/event/2026-trail-running-film-festival-run-expo/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:visit_palmer
X-SOURCE:Visit Palmer
DTSTART;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260416T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260416T200000
DTSTAMP:20260321T180104
CREATED:20260221T165351Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260221T165351Z
UID:8016-1776360600-1776369600@visitpalmer.com
SUMMARY:2026 Trail Running Film Festival & Run Expo
DESCRIPTION:TRFF has become a celebration for the trail running community\, highlighting the spirit of adventure\, perseverance\, and connections to nature that make trail running a unique and thrilling experience. As we gear up for the 2026 edition\, our commitment to showcasing the most compelling and diverse stories in trail running remains unwavering. Our mission is to celebrate running as a universal practice to explore our collective and individual potential and pursue our wildest dreams.\nBlack Wolf Endurance is proud to share these stories with you as we get ready for our own race season ahead. We hope these films will connect our community and our runners in pursuing their own adventures\, conquering their own goals\, and making their own great stories.\nOur screening of TRFF will be held on Wednesday\, April 16 at 7:00pm at the Train Depot in Palmer\, Alaska.\nDoors will open at 5:30pm for the Valley’s first mini Run Expo. Come visit with race directors and local running clubs/groups to see what running and volunteer opportunities are available to you here in the MatSu Valley.\nRun Expo Attending Groups:\nAKtive Soles\nProgressive PT\nNXNW Relays\nMatSu Running Club\nTNR Healthwise\nRun Palmer\n…and more.\n\nFilm is 90 minutes in length with one intermission.\nBe ready for a fun night of community with some special surprises and many giveaways in store!\nPalmer Train Depot  S. Valley Way Palmer
URL:https://visitpalmer.com/event/2026-trail-running-film-festival-run-expo/
END:VEVENT
