BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Connect Mat-Su": "https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/the-roaming-playroom-together-time-at-lekker-coffee-9/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:connect_matsu
X-SOURCE:Connect Mat-Su
DTSTART;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260418T143000
DTEND;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260418T163000
DTSTAMP:20260321T180057
CREATED:20260309T193801Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260322T012212Z
UID:10012863-1776522600-1776529800@www.connectmatsu.org
SUMMARY:The Roaming Playroom: "Together Time" at Lekker Coffee
DESCRIPTION:That Thing Goin On is excited to announce a new community offering: The Roaming Playroom!\nThe Roaming Playroom will be hosting weekly “Together Time” at Lekker Coffee and Baking Co right in downtown Palmer.\n“Together Time” means sharing life in shared spaces – where grownups stay\, kids play\, and community grows.\nThe Roaming Playroom curates pop-up play spaces for parents to slow down\, eat\, and drink in public without rushing\, while also spending quality time with their children and connecting with other community members.\nStarting March 10\, come visit us at Lekker Coffee and Baking Co on:\nTuesdays from 12:30pm-2:30pm\nand\nSaturdays from 2:30pm-4:30pm\nYou bring your people\, I’ll bring my people\, and lets build some community together!
URL:https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/the-roaming-playroom-together-time-at-lekker-coffee-9/
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/webp:https://www.connectmatsu.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/The-roaming-playroom.webp
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE-URLS:{"Connect Mat-Su": "https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/free-movie-cars/"}
X-SOURCE-ID:connect_matsu
X-SOURCE:Connect Mat-Su
DTSTART;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260418T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Anchorage:20260418T200000
DTSTAMP:20260321T180057
CREATED:20260312T191804Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260322T012213Z
UID:10012885-1776533400-1776542400@www.connectmatsu.org
SUMMARY:Free Movie - Cars
DESCRIPTION:FREE MOVIE NIGHT – Disney Pixar’s CARS\nSPECIAL – Kids – design a box car and bring it to a mini (indoor) drive in movie! Best car design gets a prize!\n“While traveling to California to race The King and Chick Hicks in the Piston Cup Championship\, Lightning McQueen falls out of his trailer and winds up in a run-down town called Radiator Springs. He slowly befriends the town’s odd residents\, including Sally\, Doc Hudson and Mater. When it comes time for him to leave\, the championship is no longer his top priority.” – Rotten Tomatoes\nPopcorn\, candy\, and drinks available for purchase. 18 and under must be accompanied by and adult.\nPopcorn\, candy and drinks available for purchase. Gates open at 5:30pm and movie starts at 6pm
URL:https://www.connectmatsu.org/event/free-movie-cars/
END:VEVENT
